{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17531962","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17531962"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T16:21:03+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T16:21:03+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14641"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14641","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14641"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.08,0.68,0.01,0.13,0.1]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7334"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"103740"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7334","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7334"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14641"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"86161"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"7"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"27"},{"type":"tags","id":"34"},{"type":"tags","id":"45"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"191"},{"type":"tags","id":"380"},{"type":"tags","id":"2040"},{"type":"tags","id":"2778"},{"type":"tags","id":"3505"},{"type":"tags","id":"4974"},{"type":"tags","id":"4975"},{"type":"tags","id":"4976"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11633"},{"type":"tags","id":"11635"},{"type":"tags","id":"11641"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"17900"},{"type":"contributions","id":"36955"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43547"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44740"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"103740","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/103740"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 56-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic with a three-month history of tingling and numbness in her right hand, particularly affecting her thumb, index and middle fingers. Her symptoms are worse at night and when typing. She works as a data entry clerk, typing for eight hours daily. She has a history of type 2 diabetes mellitus and obesity with a body mass index of 32 kg/m\u003Csup\u003E2\u003C/sup\u003E. Her medications include metformin and gliclazide.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. Percussion over the median nerve at the wrist produces tingling in the distribution of the nerve. Holding the wrist in maximal flexion for 30 seconds reproduces her symptoms. Two-point discrimination is reduced over the lateral three digits. Muscle power and reflexes in the upper limbs are normal.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate first line management approach to optimise return to work?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Corticosteroid injection","Night splinting with workplace modifications","Change of occupation","Referral for surgical decompression","Physiotherapy exercises"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with typical symptoms and signs of carpal tunnel syndrome (CTS), with occupational risk factors (repetitive typing) and medical risk factors (diabetes, obesity). The goal of treatment is to prevent progression and enable continued employment with minimal symptoms.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENight splinting with workplace modifications\u003C/strong\u003E is the most appropriate first-line management strategy. Night splinting keeps the wrist in a neutral position, reducing pressure on the median nerve during sleep. Workplace modifications such as ergonomic keyboard positioning, regular breaks, and proper posture are essential for addressing occupational factors. This combined approach addresses both nocturnal symptoms and occupational contributors.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECorticosteroid injection \u003C/strong\u003Emay provide temporary symptom relief but does not address the underlying occupational factors contributing to the condition. While injections can be useful as part of a comprehensive management plan, they should not be the sole intervention in a working patient.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChange of occupation\u003C/strong\u003E is an overly drastic measure before attempting conservative management strategies. Most patients with CTS can continue their usual occupation with appropriate modifications and treatment.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReferral for surgical decompression\u003C/strong\u003E would be premature without first trying conservative measures, especially given the relatively short duration of symptoms. Surgery is typically reserved for cases that fail conservative management or show evidence of severe compression with muscle wasting or sensory loss.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPhysiotherapy exercises\u003C/strong\u003E have limited evidence in the management of CTS and would not adequately address the mechanical compression of the median nerve or the occupational factors.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Night splinting is the first-line conservative treatment for carpal tunnel syndrome in working-age patients.","Occupational modification is essential for successful management of carpal tunnel syndrome.","Corticosteroid injection provides temporary relief but does not address underlying occupational factors.","Surgical decompression should be reserved for cases which cannot be managed by more conservative approaches, or in cases of severe nerve compression with muscle wasting or sensory loss"],"references":["Genova A, Dix O, Saefan A, Thakur M, Hassan A. Carpal Tunnel Syndrome: A Review of Literature. Cureus. 2020;12(3):e7333. Published 2020 Mar 19. doi:10.7759/cureus.7333. Available online at ; https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC7164699/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"86161"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14641"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"86161","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/86161"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-05-26T10:26:12+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-05-26T10:27:20+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7334"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"103740"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"7","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/7"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udde0","name":"Neurology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:45+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"27","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/27"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc77","name":"Occupational/Environmental Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"34","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/34"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddb4","nam